"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The function get_active_figure() is designed to return the current active figure, but it does not check if the figure is actually active before trying to add text to it. The ax.text() method is called on the ax object, which is associated with a figure that has already been closed. This will raise an error because the axes object is no longer valid after plt.close() is called.\", \"patch\": \"18c18\\n< ax.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\")\\n---\\n> if ac_fig is not None:\\n>     ax.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\")\\n\"}"